data.text: Directory of MPs of Ukrainian Parliament of sixth convocation (by faction, as of January 28, 2009) Party of Regions Members: 175 Faction leader: Viktor Yanukovych Deputy leaders: Hanna Herman, Vasyl Dzharty, Oleksandr Yefremov, Oleksandr Lavrynovych, Serhiy Lyovochkin, Volodymyr Makeyenko, Andriy Klyuyev, Serhiy Klyuyev, Borys Kolesnikov, Oleksandr Peklushenko, Volodymyr Rybak. YANUKOVYCH, Viktor Fedorovych; born 1950; leader, Party of Regions; former prime minister (2002-04; 2006-07) and presidential candidate (2004); former Donetsk Region governor (1997-2002) CHORNOVIL, Taras Vyacheslavovych; born 1964; Party of Regions member; member of previous parliaments (from People's Movement of Ukraine (Rukh), 2000-02; from Viktor Yushchenko's Our Ukraine bloc, 2002-06; from Party of Regions, 2006-07); son of late nationalist party leader and Soviet era dissident Vyacheslav Chornovil BOHOSLOVSKA, Inna Hermanivna; born 1960; unaffiliated; former leader of Viche party (2001-07); member of previous convocation of Parliament (1998-2002); former deputy justice minister (2007) SHUFRYCH, Nestor Ivanovych; born 1966; Party of Regions member; former member, first deputy head of United Social Democratic Party of Ukraine (1996-2007); member of previous convocations of Parliament (1998-2002; 2002-06); former emergencies minister (2006-07) AZAROV, Mykola Yanovych; born 1947; Party of Regions member; former first deputy prime minister and finance minister (2004, 2006-07); former acting prime minister (2005); former head of State Tax Administration (1996-2002); member of previous convocations of Parliament (1994-98, 2006) AKHMETOV, Rinat Leonidovych; born 1966; Party of Regions member; member of previous convocation of Parliament (2006-07); president of Shakhtar Football Club (Donetsk) (since 1996); owner of 90 per cent stake in System Capital Management company; Ukraine's richest businessman (according to Polish magazine Wprost) YEFREMOV, Oleksandr Serhiyovych; born 1954; Party of Regions member; member of previous convocation of Parliament (2006-07); president of Luhansk regional branch of Ukrainian Union of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs; former Luhansk Region governor (1998- 2005); board chairman of Ukrkomunbank commercial bank (since 1996) ZVYAHILSKIY, Yukhym Leonidovych; born 1933; Party of Regions member; chairman of board of lessees of Zasyadko coal mine (Donetsk Region); director of Zasyadko coal mine (1979-92); member of previous convocations of Parliament (1990-94, from Apr 1994; 1998- 2002, 2002-06, 2006-07); former first deputy prime minister (1993); former acting prime minister (1993-94) KOLESNIKOV, Borys Viktorovych;
